    "form_header_text": "FY2027 Appropriations Form",
    "form_instructions_text": "Article I of the Constitution gives Congress the power to pass laws that spend money from the federal treasury. Congress approves federal spending through annual bills known as appropriations. Hearing directly from constituents and stakeholders about priorities for federal spending is essential to Rep. Larsen's work as Congress crafts spending bills for Fiscal Year 2027.\n\nPlease complete the below form by Friday, March 6, 2026 at 5 PM Pacific Time/8 PM Eastern Time, to request that Rep. Larsen make a submission to the House Appropriations Committee.\n\nDistinguishing types of requests:\nProgrammatic Request: a request to fund a specific program at a specified level.\nLanguage Request: a request to include specific bill or report language that does not direct funding to a particular entity but encourages, urges, or directs some type of action by an agency.\n\nRep. Larsen will not submit all requests. Priority will be given to requests with a connection to Washington's Second District. If you have multiple requests, you must submit multiple forms.\n\nPlease do not use this form for Community Project Funding (earmark) requests.",
